<task id="012" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add WorkspaceOptions.SummarizePlaybookCode (FR-04) + fix ADR-018 violation at WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254</title>
    <phase>1: §1.7 Stable Codes Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>004</dependencies>
    <blocks>013,019</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, config, ADR-018</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies typed-options surface + endpoint code; tags include 'bff-api'; ADR-018 binding; FR-04 acceptance is exact-zero-call-sites grep</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add `SummarizePlaybookCode` (string) property to `WorkspaceOptions.cs` and migrate `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254` from raw `IConfiguration["Workspace:SummarizePlaybookId"]` indexer reads to `IOptions&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;.Value.SummarizePlaybookCode` typed reads. Implements FR-04 + fixes the existing ADR-018 violation. This task does NOT migrate the consumer to stable-code resolution — that is task 019; this task only fixes the option shape so 019 can complete cleanly.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in IOptions binding + ASP.NET Core minimal-API DI.</role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceOptions.cs` has a new `SummarizePlaybookCode` string property bound from `Workspace:SummarizePlaybookCode` config key. `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254` uses `IOptions&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;` (or `IOptionsMonitor`) instead of `IConfiguration["..."]` indexer. Existing config keys preserved (`Workspace:SummarizePlaybookId` continues to bind to existing GUID property for backward-compat until task 019 retires it). Unit test asserts the option binds correctly.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-04 acceptance: `IConfiguration["Workspace:SummarizePlaybookId"]` returns zero call sites. The current code at `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254` violates ADR-018 (raw indexer reads). This task is the prerequisite shape fix that unblocks task 013 (4-code extension) and task 019 (consumer migration to stable code). Task 019 will REPLACE the `SummarizePlaybookCode` use in the endpoint with `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync(options.SummarizePlaybookCode, ...)`; this task only ensures the typed-option exists to feed it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/WorkspaceOptions.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Workspace/WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>config/appsettings.Development.json (or appsettings.json)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Options/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Typed options REQUIRED; raw `IConfiguration[]` indexer reads BANNED in new/modified code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — inject `IOptions&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;` (or `IOptionsMonitor`) directly; no `IServiceProvider.GetService&lt;T&gt;()`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Endpoint stays in `Api/Workspace/` — no AI facade boundary change.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; expect ≤0.05 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-04 acceptance: `grep "IConfiguration\\[\"Workspace:SummarizePlaybookId\"\\]" src/` returns zero matches AFTER this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT modify the endpoint's resolution logic (task 019 owns that). This task only changes the option shape.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve backward-compat — existing `SummarizePlaybookId` property remains so deployed configs don't break mid-migration.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
